A pine tree with snow, near the Togetsukyo bridge in Arashiyama.
</p>
<p class="jp">
       嵐山の渡月橋近くにある雪をかぶった松の木。 
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Snow" /><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Black and White" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A pine tree with snow, near the Togetsukyo bridge in Arashiyama. 嵐山の渡月橋近くにある雪をかぶった松の木。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R02015_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R02015_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Oi River in the Snow・雪の大堰川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250224/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Oi River in the Snow・雪の大堰川" /><published>2025-02-24T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-24T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/snow</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250224/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        Another snowfall in Kyoto, perhaps the last of the season. Walking along the Oigawa river, while a boat travels to the Hoshinoya Resort around the bend.
</p>


<p class="jp">
       京都にまた雪が降った。おそらく今シーズン最後だろう。大堰川沿いを歩きながら、カーブを曲がったところにある星のやリゾートに船を走らせる。
  
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Snow" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Another snowfall in Kyoto, perhaps the last of the season. Walking along the Oigawa river, while a boat travels to the Hoshinoya Resort around the bend.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R02031.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R02031.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Red, White, &amp;amp; Green・赤・白・緑</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250222/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Red, White, &amp;amp; Green・赤・白・緑" /><published>2025-02-22T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-22T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/chikurin</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250222/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        On the bamboo path, from the big snow a few weeks back.
</p>


<p class="jp">
       数週間前の大雪のとき、竹林で撮った。
  
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Bamboo Grove" /><category term="Snow" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[On the bamboo path, from the big snow a few weeks back.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01228.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01228.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Pink Ume・紅梅</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250221/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Pink Ume・紅梅" /><published>2025-02-21T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-21T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ume</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250221/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        Ume blossoms on the Katsura River, out the window at Restaurant Nishiki.
</p>


<p class="jp">
       レストラン錦の窓から見える桂川の紅梅。
  
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Ume blossoms on the Katsura River, out the window at Restaurant Nishiki.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_DSCF0742_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_DSCF0742_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ume at Seiryo-ji・清涼寺の梅花</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250220/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ume at Seiryo-ji・清涼寺の梅花" /><published>2025-02-20T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-20T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/seiryoji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250220/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        Ume blossoms have been late coming out this year, but they are starting to appear, such as this tree in Arashiyama's Seiryo-ji temple.
</p>
 <p class="en">
          (Ume are commonly called plum blossoms in English, but are actually a relative of the apricot.)
</p>

<p class="jp">
        今年は梅の開花が遅かったが、嵐山・清涼寺のこの木のように、咲き始めている。
  
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Flowers" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Ume blossoms have been late coming out this year, but they are starting to appear, such as this tree in Arashiyama's Seiryo-ji temple. (Ume are commonly called plum blossoms in English, but are actually a relative of the apricot.)]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01959.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01959.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama Morning・朝の嵐山</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250219/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama Morning・朝の嵐山" /><published>2025-02-19T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-19T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/togetsukyo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250219/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        The sun shines while a few snowflakes continue to fall at the Togetsukyo bridge in Arashiyama.
</p>

<p class="jp">
        嵐山の渡月橋で雪がちらつく中、太陽が輝いている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Morning" /><category term="Snow" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The sun shines while a few snowflakes continue to fall at the Togetsukyo bridge in Arashiyama.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_DSCF0722.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_DSCF0722.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Shimadai・嶋臺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250217/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Shimadai・嶋臺" /><published>2025-02-17T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-17T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/shimadai</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250217/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        Built for an Edo era sake wholesaler, this traditional machiya and warehouse has a new life as the Shimadai Gallery. Taken on Fujichome Provia 100F film.
</p>

<p class="jp">
        江戸時代の酒問屋のために建てられたこの伝統的な町家と蔵は、嶋臺（しまだい）ギャラリーとして新たな人生を歩んでいる。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Film" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Built for an Edo era sake wholesaler, this traditional machiya and warehouse has a new life as the Shimadai Gallery. Taken on Fujichome Provia 100F film.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R02002.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R02002.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kyoto Marathon・京都マラソン</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250216/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kyoto Marathon・京都マラソン" /><published>2025-02-16T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-16T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kyoto-marathon</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250216/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        After ~100 shots of runners, I started dragging the shutter to see if I could make something more interesting...
</p>

<p class="jp">
        ランナーを～100枚ほど撮った後、もっと面白いものができないかとシャッターを引きずり始めた。
</p>

